description: Check how much it costs to submit Agricultural Credits applications using form AC1 to form AC8.

details.body:
Agricultural Credits Department fees

Forms Type of application Apply by post or DX
AC1, AC2 Registration £5 per name
AC7 Rectification of an entry £5 per name
AC3 Cancellation of an entry £5 per name
AC4 Certificate of cancellation £5 per name
AC8 Personal search in the register or
of a filed memorandum		 £5 per name
AC5 Certified copy of a filed memorandum £4 per name
AC6 Official search* £4 per name

Receive the result by phone

*When you apply for an official search to be made in the Agricultural Credits Register, using form AC6 you can request that the result of search be posted or telephoned. It costs £5 per call (minimum fee), in addition to the £4 per name fee payable for the official search.

How to pay fees

You can pay for services and substantive applications by:

  • variable direct debit, if you have a Business e-services account
  • cheque or postal order - make payable to ‘HM Land Registry’ and send with your application to our Agricultural Credits Department

More information

This guide is based on the statutory provision of the Agricultural Credits Fees Order 1985, which came into effect on 1 June 1985 and still applies.

If you are still unsure of the fee, please use our online form to contact us.
